My first time in Austin.

04:42.560 --> 04:48.360
All the way from Japan, which is, I was always like, you know, okay, I'll visit Andrew when I go to Japan.

04:48.560 --> 04:51.700
I wanted to do a little Japan tour, so it's cool to, thank you for coming out here.

04:51.920 --> 04:52.280
You're welcome.

04:52.280 --> 04:57.860
Why don't we just start there, actually, with the kind of alien DMT connection?

04:58.940 --> 05:04.980
I was actually listening to you on my buddy Michael's podcast, Third Eye Drops,

05:04.980 --> 05:09.120
and you were talking about John Mack and alien abductions

05:09.120 --> 05:16.980
and how a lot of these alien abduction experiences really connect or seem to pattern match to what people experience on DMT.

05:16.980 --> 05:27.240
Yeah, I mean, they're not the same, but really, well, from the beginning of DMT research back in,

05:27.680 --> 05:34.300
so DMT was discovered in 1956 by this Hungarian physician called Stephen Zara.

05:34.980 --> 05:38.480
This was when Hungary was a communist state.

05:38.480 --> 05:44.700
And from the very first study that he did, I mean, at first he injected himself.

05:44.840 --> 05:50.760
I mean, this was kind of the good old days of science when scientists injected new drugs into themselves.

05:51.480 --> 05:51.580
Yeah.

05:53.420 --> 06:02.960
So he discovered after injecting it into himself that it was quite clearly very, very psychedelic.

06:02.960 --> 06:13.020
This kind of rush of highly complex geometric imagery that kind of overwhelmed him, seized control of him.

06:13.640 --> 06:20.820
So he knew then that this was something special, something quite different to the drugs that were known at the time,

06:20.900 --> 06:23.720
LSD, mescaline, psilocybin.

06:24.240 --> 06:30.700
This seemed to kind of transcend that and transport you to some alternate reality.

06:30.700 --> 06:39.040
So he started injecting with the drug into people, colleagues, basically, who worked at the same hospital.

06:39.740 --> 06:49.420
And even in those very first studies, it was quite obvious that these individuals were not just being transported to other worlds,

06:49.500 --> 06:56.060
but these were populated worlds and that there were what seemed to be kind of intelligent beings,

06:56.060 --> 07:09.280
including little diminutive creatures, multitudinous creatures, lively beings that now we would recognize as elves or machine elves in Terence McKenna parlance.

07:09.280 --> 07:23.520
But when Rick Strassman picked up the mantle in the early 90s, and he did a much larger study with 60 volunteers of various, various doses of DMT,

07:23.520 --> 07:37.480
and a not insignificant number of these individuals reported experiences that would not raise an eyebrow if they had appeared in books by John Mack.

07:37.600 --> 07:46.520
So kind of alien abduction type experiences where people are brought into some kind of highly sophisticated technological environment

07:46.520 --> 08:01.240
where there are beings, often a number of like orderlies, less senior beings who were kind of performing the work and, you know, analyses and measurements, scanning and all this kind of stuff.

08:01.240 --> 08:12.140
And then often there was one, like Top Dog, who was kind of in the background, but had a very strong presence, kind of overseeing or supervising the procedure.

08:13.140 --> 08:21.980
And then they'd often be taken on kind of a tour of this craft or technological place,

08:21.980 --> 08:32.240
meetings with highly intelligent, highly advanced, non-human beings, and then brought safely back into the normal waking world.

08:32.840 --> 08:45.500
And this, if you, this kind of scenario is precisely what John Mack's abductees or experiences, as he used to call them, were kind of reporting.

08:45.500 --> 08:48.460
So it didn't escape John Mack's attention.

08:48.460 --> 08:51.680
I mean, people were asking him, you know, have you heard about DMT?

08:51.800 --> 08:58.560
Because what you're, what you're talking about sounds a lot like what people are reporting under the influence of DMT.

08:58.740 --> 09:09.020
And I think, you know, Rick Strassman also said, you know, if, if we removed all references to DMT in many of the reports from my volunteers,

09:09.500 --> 09:15.200
would anyone be able to distinguish them from the reports of alien abductees?

09:15.200 --> 09:27.540
And I think towards the end, you know, as, as John Mack progressed through his abduction career, if you want to put it like that,

09:27.540 --> 09:42.780
he's, he, he was, he became less convinced that this was a purely physical nuts and bolts phenomenon where people were actually being removed from their,

09:42.920 --> 09:46.300
their beds at night and taken onto actual physical crafts.

09:46.300 --> 09:56.160
But he started to feel like this was some kind of non-physical process.

09:56.400 --> 09:56.480
Yeah.

09:56.580 --> 10:07.300
These, many of his subjects reported going to old environments that weren't, that didn't seem to be physical.

10:07.300 --> 10:07.860
Yeah.

10:08.060 --> 10:18.660
So places that were had kind of higher dimensional spaces, beings that were very similar to the types of beings that people encounter in DMT.

10:18.820 --> 10:29.120
So he, he kind of shifted towards a more spiritual or metaphysical or non-physical explanation for these abduction experiences.

10:29.120 --> 10:35.140
And a little context for the audience, John Mack was the head of the Harvard psychiatry department in the nineties.

10:35.640 --> 10:41.640
And he was actually childhood friends with a guy named Bud Hopkins, who was documenting a lot of these sort of abduction experiences.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.120
And he started to take a deep dive.

10:44.180 --> 10:50.040
He was actually friends with Thomas Kuhn, who wrote Structure of Scientific Revolutions.

10:50.040 --> 10:52.840
And he was like, I don't know, maybe some of this alien stuff is real.

10:52.840 --> 10:59.580
And Kuhn was like, yeah, this, you know, basically you should, you know, try to maintain the null hypothesis for as long as possible.

10:59.580 --> 11:05.040
But even though you sit on a respectable perch at Harvard, you should actually dive into this.

11:05.120 --> 11:06.360
He started to dive into it.

11:06.380 --> 11:07.780
He started to take it very seriously.

11:07.780 --> 11:12.340
He was like, these people are reporting events that they feel are very, very real.

11:12.540 --> 11:15.220
They have no mental health history prior or after.

11:15.220 --> 11:26.420
And so it's interesting that you say that he sort of, you know, starts to view them as more spiritual or taking place in maybe a realm apart from the physical.

11:26.420 --> 11:39.000
He was also very inspired by Stanislav Grof and holotropic breathwork, where the goal is actually to, I think, endogenously release DMT or something at the end of the breathwork.

11:39.000 --> 11:52.600
And so if that's inspired Mac to that extent, and then Mac would use that in his practice with a lot of the abductees in order for them to recall their experiences, maybe that adds to your point.

11:52.900 --> 12:01.980
But I will say that some of these abductees have physical marks and things and implants and stuff where it's like, do you have an explanation for that?

12:02.020 --> 12:02.800
Have you thought of that?

12:02.800 --> 12:11.000
Yeah, I mean, I think the line between the physical and the non-physical is not always clear.

12:11.200 --> 12:11.920
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

12:11.920 --> 12:12.200
Right?

12:12.320 --> 12:16.180
So it's like you can't really, it's hard to get at.

12:16.320 --> 12:23.440
There is obviously what we would consider to be a physical aspect, but there also seems to be a very non-physical aspect.

12:23.780 --> 12:27.240
And I just don't think we, as humans, we really understand.

12:27.240 --> 12:38.280
I think maybe if we were able to observe this from a higher perspective and kind of an overview, like a bird's eye view of reality, it might be obvious what's going on here.

12:38.380 --> 12:43.060
But I just, I just think it's useful to be able to distinguish between the physical.

12:43.440 --> 12:53.640
It's kind of instructive to distinguish between the physical and the non-physical, but actually sometimes you point out it's maybe a combination of the physical and the non-physical.

12:53.640 --> 13:04.460
And I feel like people, like if they were to point to a dividing line where the physical and the non-physical sort of divested, it would be Descartes or something in the kind of proverbial, you know.

13:04.460 --> 13:21.400
But if you look at Descartes, like how that divestiture actually occurred is he was talking about, he was doing thought experiments about a demon controlling your entire perceptive epistemology in some almost, you know, proto like VR headset that could be reality.

13:21.400 --> 13:25.980
And all you could know is that your own thoughts were yours or something.

13:26.440 --> 13:26.600
Yeah.

13:26.780 --> 13:28.280
And so that's a pretty trippy thought.

13:28.280 --> 13:29.340
It is.

13:29.460 --> 13:49.480
And I actually, that's kind of an interesting point because Groff actually, in one of his books, he said, look, if there are advanced intelligent beings, you know, aliens that are kind of non-physical, discarnate, everywhere and nowhere,

13:49.480 --> 13:58.400
then the way that they would appear to us would be dismissed as hallucination.

13:58.400 --> 14:01.820
They would kind of interact with our brain directly.

14:02.060 --> 14:11.820
They wouldn't have to kind of materialize, so to speak, in a true quote unquote physical form, but they would interact with us directly with our brain.

14:11.820 --> 14:32.200
And I think that's actually what's going on, whether it's Descartes' demon, but I think when you smoke DMT, for example, what I think is happening or what I've come to believe or lean towards an explanation for what's happening,

14:32.200 --> 14:43.880
is that you have these intelligences that don't have a physical form, they don't have a form that could even be represented in any kind of visual form.

14:43.880 --> 14:55.240
These are completely non-physical discarnate beings, but DMT somehow gives them access to our neural machinery.

14:56.380 --> 14:59.600
And so they are, I believe, directing the visions.

14:59.600 --> 15:03.000
I believe the DMT world to be what I call a directed world.

15:03.480 --> 15:05.120
I don't think you're going anywhere.

15:05.780 --> 15:12.780
I don't think you're peeking through into another world because that's not how perception works.

15:12.780 --> 15:21.780
Perception works by your brain building this model, which is then tested against sensory inputs from the environment.

15:22.120 --> 15:28.180
You never have direct access to the so-called external world or the environment.

15:28.180 --> 15:31.740
And it's the same in the DMT experience.

15:31.980 --> 15:37.160
You're not seeing the DMT world, whatever that might mean.

15:37.540 --> 15:44.600
You're simply giving access to these intelligent agents, giving them access to your brain.

15:44.860 --> 15:46.100
So you don't break through.

15:46.220 --> 15:48.640
I always say you don't break through into the DMT world.

15:48.640 --> 15:55.620
It's the DMT world or the intelligences within this space that break through into you.

15:56.180 --> 15:58.400
They seize control.

15:58.580 --> 16:03.240
They kind of commandeer this world modeling machinery in your brain.

16:03.440 --> 16:05.580
And they direct your visions.

16:06.120 --> 16:09.940
Do they have, in your opinion, and this is maybe a philosophical question,

16:09.940 --> 16:18.500
do these entities have control prior to you taking DMT and then you are able to notice it through DMT?

16:18.680 --> 16:24.000
Or are you like, do they take control like when you take DMT?

16:24.240 --> 16:29.280
Well, I'm going to give the optimistic answer, which is to say it's DMT.

16:29.280 --> 16:38.780
I mean, what DMT does is it generates this very fluid and dynamic state of the brain, of the cortex,

16:39.180 --> 16:41.740
this outer layer of the brain that constructs your world model.

16:42.240 --> 16:51.020
And some very recent neuroimaging data actually show that DMT makes the brain much more sensitive

16:51.020 --> 16:58.460
to being perturbed by external sensory or other types of input.

16:58.600 --> 17:04.560
So it becomes primed, if you like, to be commandeered, taken over in this way.

17:04.560 --> 17:10.040
So I'd like to think that they don't have access in the normal waking state,

17:10.120 --> 17:12.620
because that's kind of a horrifying thought, right?

17:13.200 --> 17:16.620
But in the presence of DMT, they gain access.

17:16.620 --> 17:25.360
Your brain is in a much more vulnerable or susceptible state to being commandeered by these intelligences.

17:25.900 --> 17:27.400
And that's clearly what happens.

17:27.520 --> 17:34.940
People describe this massive, overwhelming rush of information that floods their brain,

17:35.240 --> 17:39.840
complex imagery, mathematical imagery, blueprints,

17:39.840 --> 17:47.360
and just completely alien stuff that has no relationship to their normal waking experience.

17:47.680 --> 17:52.940
And I think that is kind of the hallmark of them basically saying,

17:53.140 --> 17:58.800
you know, we have control now for the next five minutes or so.

17:59.860 --> 18:04.020
And then they kind of show you what they want to show you,

18:04.120 --> 18:06.560
which is sometimes a performance.

18:06.560 --> 18:11.440
They kind of say, look at this, look what we can do.

18:12.100 --> 18:14.520
And they will show these.

18:14.640 --> 18:21.000
They will often display these impossible, higher dimensional, beautiful objects

18:21.000 --> 18:23.140
that kind of morph in front of your eyes.

18:23.140 --> 18:27.300
Or they will hold up screens with these impossibly complex imagery.

18:27.300 --> 18:33.040
They will perform beings like elves or harlequins or jokers and jesters.

18:33.040 --> 18:36.360
And they will kind of, they will say, look, look at this.

18:36.560 --> 18:37.660
This is impossible.

18:37.660 --> 18:38.960
And yet we're doing it.

18:39.260 --> 18:41.280
You know, they're doing it with your brain.

18:41.380 --> 18:46.680
Your brain is like the stage that they are using for this performance.

18:47.480 --> 18:50.300
And then in other cases, it's more serious.

18:50.300 --> 18:52.660
There seems to be some kind of agenda.

18:53.120 --> 18:56.140
People often describe like they were waiting for me.

18:56.140 --> 18:59.080
And they knew, they weren't surprised.

18:59.260 --> 19:01.320
I was very fucking surprised.

19:01.860 --> 19:04.140
But they weren't surprised at all.

19:04.240 --> 19:05.760
They had a place ready for me.

19:05.820 --> 19:06.880
And they slotted me in.

19:06.920 --> 19:08.140
And they started working.

19:08.340 --> 19:10.980
There's scanning and lights flashing and beeping.

19:11.300 --> 19:15.940
And just, they knew exactly what to do in the short time available.

19:15.940 --> 19:22.440
So, yeah, it's, um, so this brings up a question of like discernment.

19:22.480 --> 19:27.520
Like if, I don't know, you're talking about harlequin jesters and, you know, tricksters

19:27.520 --> 19:28.340
and stuff.

19:28.340 --> 19:33.040
And, um, you know, on the other hand, you know, there's things with serious agendas for

19:33.040 --> 19:33.400
you.

19:33.800 --> 19:41.220
Um, how do you, uh, go into a trip like this and be able to, and fend for yourself and go

19:41.220 --> 19:45.900
in with a specific intention where you're not, you know, the product being used, but you,

19:45.940 --> 19:51.680
you have a specific goal or intention, or I don't know, it can be heel, very healing for

19:51.680 --> 19:56.520
a lot of people, for example, maybe, maybe that's the, the sort of positive outcome version

19:56.520 --> 19:58.560
of this, or how do you, how do you sort of dictate that?

19:58.580 --> 20:00.360
And is it, is it inherently very risky?

20:00.740 --> 20:01.860
You don't dictate it.

20:02.100 --> 20:06.700
If you try to dictate it, then you're in trouble because there's no way you cannot dictate

20:06.700 --> 20:07.180
it.

20:07.280 --> 20:08.160
I mean, that's the thing.

20:08.180 --> 20:08.820
You have to surrender.

20:08.820 --> 20:09.960
You have to surrender.

20:10.140 --> 20:15.860
I mean, you can go in with intention, um, and people do, people will go in.

20:15.940 --> 20:20.180
They will, you know, they might suffer from, I don't know, chronic headaches or depression

20:20.180 --> 20:24.980
or something that they're, they're seeking a solution to something.

20:25.500 --> 20:27.420
And they go in with that intention.

20:27.420 --> 20:32.420
And very often they will find that these beings will get to work on them, literally on their

20:32.420 --> 20:32.900
brain.

20:32.900 --> 20:42.120
Uh, and they will feel their brain being reprogrammed, um, rewired by these elf like beings or other

20:42.120 --> 20:43.940
or insectoid beings.

20:43.940 --> 20:48.600
These are the kind of two of the most, um, common types of, uh, of, of, of being.

20:48.600 --> 20:54.760
And they will, they will often achieve great relief from that, you know, their headaches stop

20:54.760 --> 20:59.500
happening, you know, or, or they feel more positive about life.

20:59.500 --> 21:01.560
And they feel like their, their depression has lifted.

21:01.780 --> 21:03.100
So that's certainly possible.

21:03.100 --> 21:10.380
It's not, it's not like it's, um, you kind of have to accept that you get what you get.

21:10.380 --> 21:15.860
Um, but at the end of the day, yes, you kind of do have to accept that you're not going to

21:15.860 --> 21:17.340
be able to control this thing.

21:17.340 --> 21:23.300
And if you try, that's, I think when bad experiences happen, when you go in there with a sense of

21:23.300 --> 21:32.280
self-assured, uh, arrogance that, you know, we humans are the top of the, the intelligence

21:32.280 --> 21:39.960
tree, you know, that DMT will obliterate any, any kind of, um, this anthropocentric belief

21:39.960 --> 21:44.280
that humans are the center of reality and that we are the most intelligent thing and that

21:44.280 --> 21:45.600
we've got it all worked out.

21:45.600 --> 21:46.400
It'll humble you.

21:46.820 --> 21:48.900
Oh, it'll humble you within seconds.

21:48.900 --> 21:53.160
It gives you what you need, not what you want when you come in, like, uh, you know,

21:53.160 --> 21:59.760
I've dabbled a little bit and I don't do much, but, um, and I, I did, I did ayahuasca once.

21:59.760 --> 22:04.780
So I've never done DMT, but I've done the ayahuasca is DMT in some sense.

22:04.780 --> 22:06.600
It's a kind of gnarly version of it.

